Installation for Redhat linux servers:
                    Always start by running the command sudo yum update
                    sudo yum install git -y                                              
                    Note that yum is the package manger for Redhat
Installation for ubuntu or Debian servers:
                    Always start by running the command sudo apt update
                    sudo apt install git -y
                    Note that apt is the package manager for Ubuntu
Installing git in windows:
                    Install gitbash from
                    https://git-scm.com/downloads
                    after installing run the command
                    git -v to see the version of git installed
